Install ruby:
$ apt-get install irb1.8 libreadline-ruby1.8 libruby libruby1.8 rdoc1.8 ruby ruby1.8 ruby1.8-dev libopenssl-ruby1.8

Install rubygems (or by apt-get):
$ wget http://rubyforge.org/frs/download.php/11289/rubygems-0.9.0.tgz
$ tar zxf rubygems-0.9.0.tgz
$ cd rubygems-0.9.0
$ sudo ruby setup.rb

Install Rails!
$ gem install rails --include-dependencies

Install development tools
$ apt-get install gcc make libc6-dev g++ automake autoconf

First, install MySQL.
$ apt-get install mysql-server mysql-client

Next, install development files for MySQL. We'll need these in order to make Ruby understand.
$ apt-get install libmysqlclient15off libmysqlclient15-dev

Then, you may install the gem
$ sudo gem install mysql

Change MySQL password:
$ mysqladmin -u root password NEW-PASSWORD

In mysql:
$ create database toolkit_development;
$ create database toolkit_test;
$ create database toolkit_production;

$ grant all on toolkit_development.* to 'toolkit'@'%' identified by 'PASSWORD';
$ grant all on toolkit_test.* to 'toolkit'@'%' identified by 'PASSWORD';
$ grant all on toolkit_production.* to 'toolkit'@'%' identified by 'PASSWORD';

Install memchache
$ apt-get install memcached

Install monit (automatic restart of mongrel_rails)
$ apt-get install monit
(config files in /etc/monit on cerberus)

Install needed gems
$ gem install actionmailer --include-dependencies
$ gem install memcache-client --include-dependencies
$ gem install mongrel --include-dependencies
$ gem install mongrel_cluster --include-dependencies
$ gem install salted_login_generator --include-dependencies
$ gem install localization_generator --include-dependencies

Your local gem should be the following ($gem list):
*** LOCAL GEMS ***

